properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 15 at 4:05PM PST until January 16 at 2:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Minor flooding expected.

* WHERE...San Juan County, Western Whatcom County, Western
Skagit County, Everett and Vicinity, Tacoma Area, Admiralty
Inlet Area, Seattle and Vicinity and Bremerton and Vicinity.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 2 PM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding possible in locations near Puget Sound
and Admiralty Inlet.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The combination of high astronomical tide,
strong winds and low pressure will result in minor tidal
overflow.

High tide at Cherry Point is around 10:00 AM PST at 10.2 feet.
High tide at Friday Harbor is around 945 AM PST at 8.6 feet.
High tide at Port Townsend is around 900 AM PST at 9.6 feet.
High tide at Seattle is around 930 AM PST at 12.8 feet.

The tidal anomaly for all locations is about 1 foot. Minor tidal
overflow problems begin in Seattle at 13.5 feet.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 2 PM PST THURSDAY
